Eric Langowski

About Me

Code is policy. In government, the choices we make when building systems and analyzing data are policy choices. I work at the intersection of Data Science & Government telling stories which make a difference and bring positive change. I received a MS in Computational Analysis & Public Policy from the University of Chicago in 2020.

I am a data scientist, award-winning historian, policymaker, and educator. I currently work at the Illinois Department of Central Management Services and on a civic tech tool to automatically file property tax appeals for low-income homeowners.

Education

University of Chicago | Chicago, IL

M.S. in Computational Analysis & Public Policy | September 2018 - June 2020

Indiana University | Bloomington, IN

B.S. in Mathematics | August 2014 - May 2018

Experience

Illinois Department of Central Management Services | Data Analyst | November 2020 to present

Property Tax Appeal Project, Illinois Institute of Technology | Consultant | June 2020 to present

Federal Emergency Management Agency | Data Analysis Specialist | August 2020 to November 2020

Center for Municipal Finance, University of Chicago | Data Scientist | May 2019 to September 2020

Office of Budget and Management, City of Chicago | Grants Management Intern | July 2019 to May 2020

Cook County Assessor’s Office | Inaugural Data Science Intern | January 2019 to September 2019
